div.div:
The non-nullable foreign key ensures that the principal entity (in this
case, Attendee) must have a dependent, one-to-one entity, Ticket. Also,
configuring the relationship as one-to-one ensures that each dependent entity,
Ticket, is unique. Notice that the Fluent API on the right has navigational
properties going both ways; each entity has a navigational property going to
the other.
